\f1\b \cf0 TikTok Caption:
\f0\b0  \'93ER tip #248: Crochet quietly in the corner until they forget you exist, then reappear with 14 emesis bags and a glow-up of rage.\'94\
The comments pour in. \'93Same.\'94 \'93They gave me Tums for internal bleeding.\'94 \'93I laughed so hard I aspirated my Ensure.\'94\
You post another TikTok. Then another. They get darker. Funnier. More surreal. One features sock puppets reenacting your last blood draw. Another is just you deadpan lip-syncing to Billie Eilish while holding a sign that says \'93Guess how many days I\'92ve been NPO?\'94\
You start seeing your story reposted \'97 stitched by other creators, quoted in Facebook groups, referenced in r/ChronicIllness. Nurses slide into your DMs. Some horrified, some helpless, some furious.\
One nurse writes: 'We tried. We really did. I paged GI four times. They never came. I\'92m so sorry.'\
Another comments under your post: 'Maybe if you ate more vegetables and didn\'92t want attention this wouldn\'92t happen.'\
You get ghosted for hours again. The charge nurse never looks you in the eye. You hear her whisper to another nurse that you\'92re \'93probably anorexic\'94 and \'93just want Dilaudid.\'94\
You lie there in silence. Because saying anything would only make it worse.\
Eventually, you\'92re discharged in paper scrubs \'97 the kind that rip when you sit down. There\'92s a shit stain on the back because no one gave you a change after the bathroom incident. Your clothes are missing. The Uber driver cancels when he sees you. You collapse on a bench outside the hospital until you can text your partner.\
He comes, 30 minutes later. He brings ginger ale and emesis bags.\
You vomit twice on the drive home. You collapse in bed. He hooks up your feed, but the formula is wrong. You throw that up, too. You email your doctor through the portal, begging for a port. No reply.\
You suck on ice chips. You take the Golytely like it\'92s punishment. You do five to ten loads of laundry a day. You cry. You think about not existing. You think about the TikTok comments. You think about your partner.\
He\'92s lived with central sensitization for 25 years. He collapsed under bridges in the Russian winter trying to get to class. He grew up in a Soviet apartment with no phone and no certainty. His mother told him, \'93Buy whatever they have,\'94 because the shelves were always empty. He has known pain longer than you\'92ve known diagnoses.\
Now he carries your emesis bag.\
You understand him more now. You love him more now. Because he never failed to understand you.\
