\f1\b \cf0 Escalated
\f0\b0  You ask for a supervisor. The psychiatrist disappears. Hours later, a nurse appears with an Ativan syringe. You refuse. A patient advocate shows up. She listens. She promises to escalate. That night, a new doctor reads your chart. It\'92s not a cure. But it\'92s the first time you feel seen.\

\f1\b Medicated Anyway
\f0\b0  You smile and play nice. You\'92re sedated anyway. The psych note says, \'93Patient responded well to anxiolytics. Likely stress-related.\'94 You\'92re discharged with no answers, paper scrubs, and a pamphlet on managing anxiety. You laugh. Then cry. Then wonder if you\'92ll come back \'97 or if next time, you won\'92t leave.\
