\f1\b \cf0 Cycle of Solidarity
\f0\b0  At your next ER visit, you see another patient \'97 scared, alone, dry-heaving. You slide over a TikTok card. You explain what to screenshot. You tell them they\'92re not crazy. You do for them what no one did for you.\

\f1\b \cb5 The Resistance
\f0\b0  You collect everything: medical records, TikToks, radiology notes. You annotate them in red pen. You build a searchable timeline. You write blog posts, make videos, host livestreams, drop screenshots. You start a newsletter called 'Gurney Dispatches.' You make a digital zine called 
\f2\i The Patient Will See You Now.
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
You start getting messages \'97 not just from fellow patients, but nurses, techs, even residents. They\'92re horrified. They want to help. They want to tell their stories too.\
You name names. You\'92re angry in public. And people join you. The ER didn\'92t believe you. But the world will.\
You stare at the ceiling. You don\'92t want to die. But you don\'92t want to live like this. Your partner walks in and says, \'93You made it through another one.\'94 And for a moment, that\'92s enough.\
